{"author":{"id":"0cc9875d3bad75fbe97fd045e9f5b480ea9f098741a193c11a1309b367e481db"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1619023358,"nonce":"TaxtUSxaWVbDz+JYQOt74cLj1MQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo1MjY4ODQyMTM="},"target":"1b67de38f3245ac3c351d1c566807b860f01b27607a455c3d579458e03e3326f","message":"This is an upstreamed issue originating here: https://github.com/GlancingMind/git-bug/issues/13\nGit-Bug supports multiple identities. Just create another one with 'git-bug user create' and list all with 'git-bug user ls'.\nIdentities can be switched by replacing the current user id for the new user id under the git-bug/identity entry in the .git/config.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1619023331,"nonce":"3+Vl/6dJvyx9HT6zisYhdo/CCMo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDgyNDIwNDEzOQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/640#issuecomment-824204139"},"message":"Comment by @MichaelMure:\n\n\u003e I'd like to re-frame that idea slighlty differently:\n\u003e\n\u003e Eventually, the webUI should be able to be used as a public portal for a project and accept external edition. That is, the maintainer of a project would put the git-bug binary on a server somewhere and run the webUI exposed on the internet. Ideally the webUI would accept external auth system like Github OAuth or others. When a new user would use those the first time, a new git-bug identity would be created in the git repo (by the go code) for later use.\n\u003e\n\u003e There is the premise of that system already:\n\u003e https://github.com/MichaelMure/git-bug/tree/master/api/auth\n\u003e https://github.com/MichaelMure/git-bug/blob/master/commands/webui.go#L92-L101\n\u003e\n\u003e All of that to say that what you are describing is **a login screen** for the webUI. With git-bug's current capability on that aspect, this login screen could have a dropdown of the existing identities. Later, support for those external auth system can be added.\n\u003e\n\u003e Note though that in a near future those existing identities might be \"locked\", in the sense that they will carry cryptographic keys and you will need to have the private key to use them.\n\u003e\n\u003e _Originally posted by @MichaelMure in https://github.com/GlancingMind/git-bug/issues/13#issuecomment-792828040_","files":null},{"type":2,"timestamp":1619023466,"nonce":"nHQ8cluRT1gOkcQ7EXFq67p3qq0=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE3OlJlbmFtZWRUaXRsZUV2ZW50NDYyNjE1NTM0OQ=="},"title":"WebUI: Add Login page with OAuth support.","was":"WebUI: Add Login page with OAuth support."},{"type":3,"timestamp":1619023595,"nonce":"wa3caHAFMAjGFIpW9dAs9MbGlPM=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDgyNDIwNjgxOQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/640#issuecomment-824206819"},"message":"[IndieAuth](https://indieweb.org/IndieAuth) might be another option to the common OAuth options.","files":null}]}